                  WILLIAM
                   LOCK
               <interp inst="t17880910-74-person651" type="surname" value="LOCK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880910-74-person651" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880910-74-person651" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I took the prisoner in our warehouse on Brewer's-quay, with a quantity of sugar concealed in the lining of his jacket; it was the 14th of August, about noon; the prisoner had worked for us, but was not employed at that time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17880910-74-person652">
                  WILLIAM
                   HOW
               <interp inst="t17880910-74-person652" type="surname" value="HOW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880910-74-person652" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880910-74-person652" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>On the 14th of August, Mr. Lock gave me charge of the prisoner; I took him to the Poultry-compter; searched him, and found the sugar; about 8 lb.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>In working out the other boat the sugar was in the hogshead; I was no further than than the half story.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17880910-74-verdict318" type="verdictDescription">
